The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Pak condemns

 Islamabad/New York, July 11 (Agencies): Pakistan President Pervez Musharraf and Prime Minister Shaukat Aziz termed the Mumbai blasts as a despicable act of terrorism.

 Pakistan strongly condemns the series of bomb blasts on commuter trains in Mumbai. This despicable act of terrorism has resulted in the loss of a large number of precious lives, said a statement issued by the Pakistan foreign office spokesperson tonight. 

 The President and Prime Minister of Pakistan have expressed condolences over the loss of innocent lives. Terrorism is a bane of our times and it must be condemned, rejected and countered effectively and comprehensively, the statement said. 

 New York beefs up security

 The US also condemned todays blasts, calling them senseless acts of violence aimed at killing innocent people.

 It was a terrible tragedy for the people of India and our thoughts and prayers are with them at this difficult time, state department spokesperson Sean McCormack said.

 In response to the blasts in Mumbai, New York tightened its transit security. The police department said it was increasing the number of random bag searches and putting hundreds of extra officers in the subways during the evening rush hour.




